[[Radiohead]] are an English [[alternative rock]] band from [[Oxfordshire]]. The band's members are [[Thom Yorke]] (lead vocals, rhythm guitar, piano, electronics), [[Jonny Greenwood]] (lead guitar, other instruments), [[Ed O'Brien]] (guitar, backing vocals), [[Colin Greenwood]] (bass guitar, synthesisers), and [[Phil Selway]] (drums, percussion).<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-10-20|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/102024.stm|title=Radiohead make double swoop  |publisher=BBC|date=1998-05-29 }}</ref> They met while attending [[Abingdon School]], a boys-only public school in [[Abingdon, Oxfordshire|Abingdon]], Oxfordshire.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-10-20|url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2003/06/13/1055220766407.html|title=Don't worry, be happy |work=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=2003-06-14 }}</ref> The band have released seven studio albums: ''[[Pablo Honey]]'' (1993), ''[[The Bends]]'' (1995), ''[[OK Computer]]'' (1997), ''[[Kid A]]'' (2000), ''[[Amnesiac]]'' (2001), ''[[Hail to the Thief]]'' (2003), and ''[[In Rainbows]]'' (2007). The first six albums were released by [[EMI]]'s [[Parlophone]] (UK and elsewhere) and [[Capitol Records|Capitol]] (USA) record labels, and the seventh was released by Radiohead themselves as a digital download, and later by [[XL Records]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-10-20|url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&searchlink=RADIOHEAD&sql=11:fxfoxql5ld6e~T2|title=Main Albums |publisher=allmusic }}</ref> Several of Radiohead's singles have appeared on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] charts, including "[[Creep (Radiohead song)|Creep]]" which peaked at number 34, "[[High and Dry]]" which peaked at number 78, and "[[Nude (song)|Nude]]" which peaked at number 37.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-10-20|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=33472&model.vnuAlbumId=1089621|title= Artist Chart History - Radiohead |work=Billboard }}</ref>

The band have received five [[BRIT Award]] nominations, but they have yet to win one. Radiohead have received the [[Best Alternative Music Performance]] award twice at the [[Grammy Awards]], for ''OK Computer'' in 1998 and ''Kid A'' in 2001. At the [[MTV Video Music Awards]], the band received the award for [[Best Art Direction]] for "[[There There]]" in 2003. Radiohead have also received the Best Act In The World Today award twice at the [[Q Awards]], in both 2001 and 2002. Overall, Radiohead received 6 awards from 29 nominations.

==BRIT Awards==
The [[BRIT Awards]] are the [[British Phonographic Industry]]'s annual pop music awards. Radiohead have received five nominations.<ref name=rotn>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-10-20|url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/artists-r/radiohead_main.htm|title=Radiohead |publisher=Rock on the Net }}</ref>

